    <section class="abstract" id="abstract">
      <div class="content">
        <h2>Abstract</h2>
        <div class="abstract-card">
          <p>
            Durra is a jewelry digital marketplace developed to connect jewelers and buyers in Bahrain, increasing the visibility of local jewelers and facilitating the shopping process for buyers. The platform is the result of careful market analysis and requirement elicitation. Upon the findings obtained, a user-centric prototype was developed to ensure a positive usability experience for users. The design was then implemented into an interactive platform that went through an iteration of testing and refinement phases to measure users' acceptance and act on their feedback. Future plans revolve around the development of a re-selling feature, real-time tracking of orders feature, and a mobile platform. Durra does also aim to integrate with more authentication and certifications providers. To conclude, all plans are to contribute to the improvement of Durra's usability and trustworthiness as envisioned by its users.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="objectives" id="objectives">
      <div class="content">
        <h2>Project Objectives</h2>
        <div class="objectives-grid">
          <div class="objective-card">
            <h3>01</h3>
            <p>To develop Durra, a dedicated digital marketplace that connects Bahraini jewelers directly with customers, enhancing the local jewelry industry's digital presence.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="objective-card">
            <h3>02</h3>
            <p>To significantly increase the visibility and market reach of Bahraini jewelers, both locally and internationally, by providing a centralized, trusted online platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="objective-card">
            <h3>03</h3>
            <p>To streamline and improve the customer journey by simplifying the process of searching for, comparing, and discovering fine jewelry pieces from multiple vendors in one place.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="objective-card">
            <h3>04</h3>
            <p>To ensure customers have access to concurrent, fair market prices and can easily compare options, fostering trust and informed decision-making.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="objective-card">
            <h3>05</h3>
            <p>To guarantee the authenticity of jewelry by leveraging and integrating official gemological authentication services, notably from DANAT (Bahrain's Institute for Pearls and Gemstones).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="objective-card">
            <h3>06</h3>
            <p>To create a secure, reliable ecosystem that benefits both jewelers and customers by offering a convenient, verified, and superior shopping experience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

